text:
As a Data Scientist at OneMagnify, I manage full-stack data science projects for Fortune 500 clients, delivering solutions that drive measurable business value. I design and implement robust ETL pipelines, create dynamic dashboards in Tableau, and develop predictive models to optimize client operations. My expertise in R, Python, SQL, and Tableau allows me to provide end-to-end support, from data engineering to business intelligence and advanced analytics, ensuring impactful and actionable insights for stakeholders.
In addition to my professional experience, I am an Adjunct Professor at West Virginia University, where I redesigned and now teach IENG 331: Computer Applications in Industrial Engineering. By integrating industry-relevant tools like SQL, Tableau, Power BI, and advanced Excel features, I prepare students for real-world data analytics careers. My curriculum emphasizes stakeholder collaboration, project-based learning, and building analytics portfolios, empowering students with practical skills they can apply early in their careers. I also teach R for data manipulation on scale, automation, and reporting, introducing tools like Quarto to demonstrate modern, scalable data workflows.
My diverse skill set is further complemented by certifications in Lean Six Sigma and Continuous Improvement, as well as hands-on teaching experience, making me adept at leading technical and cross-functional teams to deliver data-driven results.





